ines\n| {{small|Retained the [[List of ONE Championship champions#Welterweight Championship|ONE Welterweight Championship]].}}\n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n| align=center | 14\u20130\n| [[Nobutatsu Suzuki]]\n| TKO (punches)\n| [[List of ONE Championship events#ONE Fighting Championship: Reign of Champions|ONE FC 19: Reign of Champions]]\n| {{dts|2014|August|29}}\n| align=center | 1\n| align=center | 1:24\n| [[Dubai]], United Arab Emirates\n| {{small|Won the [[List of ONE Championship champions#Welterweight Championship|ONE Welterweight Championship]].}}\n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n| align=center | 13\u20130\n| Bakhtiyar Abbasov\n| Submission (arm-triangle choke)\n| [[List of ONE Championship events#ONE Fighting Championship: Honor and Glory|ONE FC 16: Honor and Glory]]\n| {{dts|2014|May|30}}\n| align=center | 1\n| align=center | 4:21\n| [[Kallang]], Singapore\n|\n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n| align=center | 12\u20130\n| [[Andrey Koreshkov]]\n| TKO (punches)\n| [[Bellator 97]]\n| {{dts|2013|July|31}}\n| align=center | 4\n| align=center | 2:58\n| [[Rio Rancho, New Mexico]], United States\n| {{small|Defended the [[List of Bellator champions#Welterweight World Championship|Bellator Welterweight World Championship]]. Later vacated title.}}\n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n| align=center | 11\u20130\n| [[Karl Amoussou]]\n| TKO (doctor stoppage)\n| [[Bellator Fighting Championships: Season Eight#Bellator LXXXVI|Bellator 86]]\n| {{dts|2013|January|24}}\n| align=center | 3\n| align=center | 5:00\n| [[Thackerville, Oklahoma]], United States\n| {{small|Defended the [[List of Bellator champions#Welterweight World Championship|Bellator Welterweight World Championship]].}}\n|-\n| {{yes2}}Win\n| align=center | 10\u20130\n| [[Douglas Lima]]\n| Decision (unanimous)\n| [[Bellator 64]]\n| {{dts|2012|April|6}}\n| align=center | 5\n| align=center | 5:00\n| [[Windsor, Ontario]], Canada\n| {{small|Defended the [[List of Bellator champions#Welterweight World Championship|Bellator Welterweight World Championship]].}}\n|-\n| {{ye