+15+year+old%2522&scp=2&st=p|work=The New York Times|title=Dean Shot Over Pin Ups|date=Apr 9, 1952}}</ref>\n|-\n|-\n| December 8, 1953\n| [[Aledo, Illinois]], United States\n| James Gipson, 17\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 26-year-old track coach George Marich was stabbed to death by 17-year-old student James Gipson in a hallway of Aledo High School. The stabbing occurred after Marich had removed Gipson and two other seniors from a study hall for creating a disturbance.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=HogRAAAAIBAJ&sjid=uOIDAAAAIBAJ&pg=5044,3631904&dq=james+gipson+george+marich&hl=en |title=Youth Stabs Track Coach |publisher=News.google.ca |date=1953-12-09 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| April 17, 1956\n| [[New York City, New York]], United States\n| Randolph Lawrence, 16\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 18-year-old Henry Smith, a student at a Bronx vocational high school, is stabbed to death by 16-year-old Randolph Lawrence, a fellow student. The stabbing was reportedly over a dispute about a [[basketball]] game.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=CZsSAAAAIBAJ&sjid=xfYDAAAAIBAJ&pg=4087,1300425&dq=school+stabbing&hl=en |title=Bronx Youth Killed in Fight at School |publisher=News.google.ca |date=1956-04-17 |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| May 4, 1956\n| [[Prince George's County, Maryland]],\nUnited States\n| Billy Ray Prevatte, 15\n| 1 dead\n| 2 injured\n| 15-year-old student Billy Prevatte fatally shot one teacher and injured two other persons at Maryland Park Junior High School in [[Prince George's County, Maryland|Prince George's County]], after he had been suspended from the school.<ref>[https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/washingtonpost_historical/access/121280833.html?dids=121280833:121280833&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&date=MAY+05%2C+1956&author=&pub=The+Washington+Post&desc=Billy+Seemed+'Nice+Boy'&pqatl=google Billy Seemed \"Nice Boy\"], [''[[The Washington Post]]''] (May 5, 1956)</ref>\n|-\n| October 20, 1956\n| [[New York City, New York]], United