e Bolden inside the school cafeteria. Police said that the shooting was gang-related.<ref>{{cite web|author=Benjamin Grove |url=http://www.lasvegassun.com/news/1998/jun/20/memories-linger-for-victims-mother/ |title=Memories linger for victim\u2019s mother |publisher=Lasvegassun.com |accessdate=2011-03-12}}</ref>\n|-\n| September 21, 1990\n| [[Houston, Texas]], United States\n| ..., 16\n| 1 dead\n|\n| A 16-year-old girl fatally stabbed her classmate, 18-year-old Anthony Johnson, in the upper back with a [[hunting knife]] in a classroom at [[Jesse H. Jones High School]], in [[Houston]], [[Texas]]; Johnson later died at [[Ben Taub Hospital]]. The suspect was then placed in the Harris County Juvenile Probation Department. It was reported that the possible motive was the victim making an insulting comment about the suspect's clothing.<ref>Markley, Melanie. \"[https://www.chron.com/CDA/archives/archive.mpl?id=1996_1371129 Studying our Schools: Challenges / Safety matters: Issue is No. 1 concern with parents].\" ''[[Houston Chronicle]]''. October 13, 1996.</ref><ref>Hanson, Eric. \"[https://www.chron.com/CDA/archives/archive.mpl?id=1990_731137 Teen fatally stabbed in classroom / Victim pays for insult to girl's shorts with life].\" ''[[Houston Chronicle]]''. September 22, 1990.</ref>\n|-\n| April 10, 1991\n| [[Glasgow]], [[Scotland]], United Kingdom\n| Barbara Glover, 16\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 16-year-old Diane Watson is stabbed to death by 16-year-old Barbara Glover at Whitehill Secondary School in the Dennistoun area of Glasgow.<ref>{{cite news| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/scotland/616759.stm|work=BBC News|title=Parents protest at killer's parole bid|date=January 24, 2000|accessdate=May 8, 2010}}</ref> Both Watson and Glover were students at the school.<ref>{{cite web|author=The Committee Office, House of Commons |url=https://publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200203/cmselect/cmcumeds/458/458w125.htm |title=Appendix 124 Memorandum submitted by Margaret and James Watson |publish