ong International Airport|Shanghai\u2013Pudong]]\n<!-- -->\n| [[DHL Aviation]] | [[Cincinnati/Northern Kentucky International Airport|Cincinnati]], [[Miami International Airport|Miami]]\n<!-- -->\n| [[EVA Air Cargo]] | [[Ted Stevens Anchorage International Airport|Anchorage]], [[Kansai International Airport|Osaka\u2013Kansai]], [[Taiwan Taoyuan International Airport|Taipei\u2013Taoyuan]]\n<!-- -->\n| [[FedEx Express]] | [[Fort Lauderdale\u2013Hollywood International Airport|Fort Lauderdale]], [[Fort Worth Alliance Airport|Fort Worth/Alliance]], [[Piedmont Triad International Airport|Greensboro]], [[Indianapolis International Airport|Indianapolis]], [[Memphis International Airport|Memphis]], [[Miami International Airport|Miami]], [[Newark Liberty International Airport|Newark]]\n<!-- -->\n| [[Korean Air Cargo]] | [[Ted Stevens Anchorage International Airport|Anchorage]], [[O'Hare International Airport|Chicago\u2013O'Hare]], [[Dallas/Fort Worth International Airport|Dallas/Fort Worth]], [[Los Angeles International Airport|Los Angeles]], [[Miami International Airport|Miami]], [[John F. Kennedy International Airport|New York\u2013JFK]]\n<!-- -->\n| [[Lufthansa Cargo]] | [[Frankfurt Airport|Frankfurt]], [[Manchester Airport|Manchester (UK)]], [[Miami International Airport|Miami]]<ref>http://199.119.0.52/webfids/webfids_cargo</ref>\n<!-- -->\n| [[Qatar Airways Cargo]] | [[Ted Stevens Anchorage International Airport|Anchorage]], [[Hamad International Airport|Doha]], [[George Bush Intercontinental Airport|Houston\u2013Intercontinental]], [[Li\u00e8ge Airport|Li\u00e8ge]], [[Luxembourg Findel Airport|Luxembourg]], [[Benito Ju\u00e1rez International Airport|Mexico City]], [[Pittsburgh International Airport|Pittsburgh]]\n<!-- -->\n| [[Singapore Airlines Cargo]] |  [[O'Hare International Airport|Chicago\u2013O'Hare]], [[Los Angeles International Airport|Los Angeles]]\n<!-- -->\n| [[Turkish Airlines Cargo]] | [[Atat\u00fcrk International Airport|Istanbul\u2013Atat\u00fcrk]], [[Shannon Airport|Shannon]]\n<!-- -->\n| [[UPS Airlines]] | [[Columbia Metropolitan Airport|Columbia (SC)]], [[Dallas/Fort Worth International Airport|Dallas/Fort Worth]], [[Louisville International Airport|Louisville]], [[Miami International Airport|Miami]], [[Philadelphia International Airport|Philadelphia]], [[Luis Mu\u00f1oz Mar\u00edn International Airport|San Juan]]\n<!-- -->\n}}\n\n== Statistics ==\n\n=== Top destinations ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size: 95%\"\n|+ '''Busiest domestic routes from ATL<!-- BTS DATA IS ONLY FOR DESTINATIONS; THIS IS NOT \"TO AND FROM\" --><br />(January 2019-December 2019)'''<ref name=\"transtats.bts.gov\">{{cite web|title=Atlanta, GA: Hartsfield\u2013Jackson Atlanta International (ATL)|url=http://www.transtats.bts.gov/airports.asp?pn=1&Airport=ATL&carrier=FACTS|publisher=[[Bureau of Transportation Statistics]]|date=January 2017|accessdate=June 22, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160308104855/http://www.transtats.bts.gov/airports.asp?pn=1&Airport=ATL&carrier=FACTS|archive-date=March 8, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref>\n|-\n! Rank\n! Airport\n! Passengers\n! Airlines\n|-\n| 1\n| [[Orlando International Airport|Orlando, Florida]]\n| 1,494,110\n| Delta, Frontier, JetBlue, Southwest, Spirit\n|-\n| 2\n| [[O'Hare International Airport|Chicago, Illinois]]\n| 1,296,520\n| American, Delta, Southwest, Spirit, United\n|-\n| 3\n| [[Fort Lauderdale\u2013Hollywood International Airport|Fort Lauderdale, Florida]]\n| 1,347,200\n| Delta, JetBlue, Southwest, Spirit\n|-\n| 4\n| [[LaGuardia Airport|New York\u2013LaGuardia, New York]]\n| 1,202,350\n| American, Delta, Frontier, Southwest\n|-\n| 5\n| [[Los Angeles International Airport|Los Angeles, California]]\n| 1,141,840\n| American, Delta, Frontier, Southwest, Spirit\n|-\n| 6\n| [[Tampa International Airport|Tampa, Florida]]\n| 1,063,250\n| Delta, Southwest, Spirit, Frontier \n|-\n| 7\n| [[Logan International Airport|Boston, Massachusetts]]\n| 979,520\n| Delta, JetBlue